info.name: Letsbook Data Scraping
info.description:
This application was made to provide a Data Scraper for a particular site (or a site that uses that book engine, making it possible to adjust to a similar one with little effort required).

The URL, object of study is:

_"_[_https://pratagy.letsbook.com.br/D/Reserva?checkin=01/05/2023&checkout=12/05/2023_](https://pratagy.letsbook.com.br/D/Reserva?checkin=01/05/2023&checkout=12/05/2023)~~_&cidade=&hotel=12&adultos=2&criancas=&destino=Pratagy+Beach+Resort+All+Inclusive&promocode=&tarifa=&mesCalendario=4/14/2023_~~_"_

The server using a REST API allows the "Pratagy" website to be scraped so that we can gather the relevant data for our purposes of using it through chatbot responses.

The database Model created for this app reflects the possibilities which code's author realized could be useful and are easy to get, once the basis for new features is set and working.

Beyond the original scope:

- The app wasn't made to function only with the predicted website, but with other ones from the same booking engine also.
- Some data that extrapole what was asked can already be found, such as PROMOCODE, which has its own function.

request.description:
This route assumes that only to parameters will be used, as follows:

> {  
"checkin": "YYYY-MM-DD",  
"checkout": "YYYY-MM-DD"  
} 
  

Using that payload, the app will search for the available dates.

And return a response such as:

`[{ "name": "Title", "description": "Text", "price":"R$xyz,00", "main_image": "https://.../abc.jpg"`

`}]`
